              <p>Donald and Melania Trump, following a day of <a href="http://www.thenewcivilrightsmovement.com/ryanjent/_school_shootings_get_a_thumbs_up_twitter_blasts_trump_for_tone_deaf_florida_photo_op">tone deaf photo-ops</a> in Parkland with first responders and survivors of the nation‚Äôs latest mass shooting, ended Friday night at a Studio 54 disco-themed party at Mar-a-Lago.</p>
<p>As HuffPost <a href="https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/trump-disco-party-after-victims-visit_us_5a88d654e4b00bc49f44e36b">noted</a>, Instagram user Sean Bianca shared an image of the first couple prior to making the account private. But the Internet is forever, and the image quickly made its rounds late Saturday:</p>
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet">
<p dir="ltr" lang="en">After meeting Parkland shooting survivors, Trump went to a disco party at Mar-a-Lago <a href="https://t.co/p4dxsHKXLy">pic.twitter.com/p4dxsHKXLy</a></p>
‚Äî Brian Tashman (@briantashman) <a href="https://twitter.com/briantashman/status/964981730775093253?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">February 17, 2018</a>
</blockquote>
<p>Some Twitter users compared it to how former President Barack Obama spent his time after the <a href="http://www.thenewcivilrightsmovement.com/tags/sandy_hook">Sandy Hook</a> tragedy:</p>
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet">
<p dir="ltr" lang="en">1: After meeting with families of the Sandy Hook victims for hours, Obama sat alone in a classroom before attending a prayer vigil. <br><br>2: After visiting with the wounded in one of the worst school shootings in U.S. history, Trump attends a Studio 54 themed party at Mar-a-Lago. <a href="https://t.co/AmZSHMyGhP">pic.twitter.com/AmZSHMyGhP</a></p>
‚Äî SeriouslyUS? (@USseriously) <a href="https://twitter.com/USseriously/status/965036862124511232?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">February 18, 2018</a>
</blockquote>
<p>Prior to making his account private, the Instagram user also reportedly updated their message to advise that the Trumps were somber:</p>
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet">
<p dir="ltr" lang="en">Immediately after visiting hospitalized survivors of the Parkland mass shooting for 20 min, Trump went to a "Studio 54" themed party at Mar-A-Lago.<br><br>A woman who posted a photo of Trump there has edited her Instagram post to say Trump "did NOT dance" and was supposedly "somber." <a href="https://t.co/0pTA9V7dIL">pic.twitter.com/0pTA9V7dIL</a></p>
‚Äî Leah McElrath üóΩ (@leahmcelrath) <a href="https://twitter.com/leahmcelrath/status/965049963104305152?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">February 18, 2018</a>
</blockquote>
<p>‚ÄúPlease take note that the President did NOT dance,‚Äù Sean Bianca wrote. ‚ÄúHe and the First Lady were there for a short time but neither was dancing around as one should have expected. Their mood was somber and they were there for a very short time.‚Äù</p>
<p>Also of note:</p>
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet">
<p dir="ltr" lang="en">Technically, he spent less than SIX MINUTES actually acknowledging the massacre‚Ä¶before being whisked off to ‚ÄúA Studio 54-themed Disco Party‚Äù. <a href="https://t.co/YOqSYTxUpf">https://t.co/YOqSYTxUpf</a> <a href="https://t.co/0Uso03uXSP">https://t.co/0Uso03uXSP</a> <a href="https://t.co/VRUotBmCIt">pic.twitter.com/VRUotBmCIt</a></p>
